Membership Database System (Oracle SQL) Created by Ashton Burgess


Project Overview:

   This project simulates a real-world membership management system built using Oracle SQL. It models a subscription-based business (such as a gym membership system) with full lifecycle tracking, automated history logging, and KPI-driven reporting.
   
   The system demonstrates how relational databases are used in operational systems and business intelligence reporting environments.

Core Objectives:
   Design a normalized relational database schema
   Implement membership lifecycle tracking
   Automate status history using PL/SQL triggers
   Build reusable KPI and analytics queries
   Generate scalable test datasets for simulation and analysis

System Architecture:
   MEMBERSHIPS
      |
      | status_id
      v
   MEMBER_STATUS (lookup table)
   
   MEMBERSHIPS
      |
      | member_id
      v
   MEMBER_STATUS_HISTORY (audit log)

Database Components:
   1. Memberships Table
      Stores core member information including:
         Member identity
         Agreement type
         Payment amount
         Current status
   2. Member Status Table
      Reference table defining valid membership states:
         Prospect
         Active
         Frozen
         Cancelled
         Collections
         Expired
   3. Status History Table
      Tracks all changes in member status over time for audit and reporting purposes.

Automation Layer:
   A PL/SQL trigger automatically manages membership lifecycle history:
      Closes previous status records when changes occur
      Inserts new status entries with timestamps
      Ensures full auditability of member status changes

Analytics and KPIs:
   The system supports operational reporting and business intelligence queries, including:
      Total active members
      Membership status distribution
      Collections rate percentage
      Revenue estimation
      Frozen and cancelled account tracking

These metrics simulate real-world reporting dashboards used in subscription-based businesses.

Data Generation:
   The project includes scalable data generation scripts:
      15-record dataset for testing
      100-record dataset for simulation
      Realistic distribution of membership statuses
      Structured financial and agreement data

Project Structure: 
   schema/        Database tables, constraints, views
   data/          Seed datasets (15 and 100 record sets)
   automation/    PL/SQL triggers for automation
   analytics/     KPI and reporting queries
   docs/          Project documentation and diagrams

Example KPI Output:
   Metric | Value
   Total Members | 100
   Active Members | 62
   Collections Rate | 8.5%
   Total Revenue | 2,340.00

Skills Demonstrated:
